      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 40
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_13_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_13",
      "description": "This 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD is a surgical-grade example of rotary excellence. The 13B-REW power plant produces exceptional compression across all rotor faces, with a refreshed vacuum rack ensuring seamless sequential turbo transition. The chassis retains its factory-spec 50/50 weight distribution and aluminum double-wishbone geometry, offering telepathic turn-in and zero bushing deflection. Power is managed via a precise 5-speed manual and a Torsen limited-slip differential, free of drivetrain lash. Meticulously maintained with an upgraded cooling stack to prevent thermal soak, this specimen represents the pinnacle of FD3S performance and mechanical preservation.",
